Empyrean International School
Principal's Message

Dear Students,

Welcome to the new academic year!

This diary is your personal companion for organising your studies. Use it diligently to record homework, important dates, and teacher's remarks every single day.

Remember, success comes from consistent effort and dedication. Work hard, stay curious, and never stop learning!

I encourage each one of you to make the best use of every opportunity this school year offers. Participate enthusiastically in all activities, respect your teachers and fellow students, and always strive to bring honour to yourself, your family, and your school.

Best wishes for a wonderful year ahead.

With warm regards,

N. L. Jharia

Principal, Empyrean International School

Ph: 9424748073

Important Notes

1
Students must arrive at least 10 minutes before the first bell.
2
Morning Assembly begins at the start of first period. Latecomers will be marked late.
3
Early departure is only allowed with written parent approval from the office.
4
Students should not wait outside the gate after school. Parents are requested to be punctual.

Academics – MP Board

Board & Curriculum

Empyrean International School follows the Madhya Pradesh Board of Secondary Education (MPBSE) curriculum from Nursery to Class 8th Standard.

Classes Offered

StageClasses
Pre-PrimaryNursery, KG 1, KG 2
PrimaryClass 1 to Class 5
Upper PrimaryClass 6 to Class 8

Examination & Assessment Pattern

TermClassesComponents
Unit Tests (Quarterly)1 – 8Regular class-based assessments every quarter
Half-Yearly Exam1 – 8Written exam after first half of session
Annual Exam1 – 8Comprehensive written exam at end of session
Continuous AssessmentNursery – KG 2Portfolio, oral, activity-based evaluation

Homework Policy

a
Daily homework is assigned by subject teachers and must be completed by the next school day.
b
Parents must check, sign, and stamp the diary every single day.
c
Projects and art work are assessed as part of continuous evaluation.
d
Repeated non-submission of homework will be reported to parents.

Empyrean International School
Student Support Services

Medical Room

First-aid is available on school premises. In case of illness, parents will be contacted immediately. Students with known medical conditions must inform the school office at the start of the session.

Transport

School transport is available from designated areas of Chhindwara. Route details are shared at the start of each session. Any change in transport must be communicated in writing to the office.

Child Protection

The school maintains a safe and inclusive environment. Bullying, harassment, or physical abuse is strictly prohibited. Students must immediately speak to their class teacher or the Principal if they feel unsafe.

Empyrean International School
Parents as Partners

Parental Responsibilities

1
Send student in full uniform with all study materials every day.
2
Ensure your ward reaches school at least 10 minutes before the first bell.
3
Check, sign, and stamp the student diary every single day.
4
Ensure homework and projects are completed before the due date.
5
Pay monthly fees in full by the 5th day of every month.
6
Attend Parent-Teacher Meetings (PTMs) as scheduled by the school.
7
Inform the school on the same day in case of absence.
8
Do not send your child with jewellery, excess money, or valuables.

Parent-Teacher Communication

Parents wishing to meet a teacher must take a prior appointment through the school office. Please do not contact teachers directly on personal phone numbers without permission. The school communicates through written circulars, the student diary, and scheduled PTMs.

Empyrean International School
School Rules & Fee Policy

Academic & Leave Rules

1
Send the student to school in full prescribed uniform with all necessary study materials daily.
2
Students must reach the school premises at least 10 minutes before the first bell.
3
Leave applications must be submitted in advance and signed by the parent/guardian.
4
In case of illness beyond two days, a medical certificate must be produced.
5
Students are expected to complete all assignments, projects, and homework on time.
6
The student diary must be brought to school every day.

Fee & Withdrawal Policy

!
STRICT RULE: Monthly fees must be paid in full by the 5th day of every month.
!
A late fee penalty of ₹100 for every 10-day delay will be applied after the due date.
!
Transfer Certificate (TC) will only be issued once all outstanding dues are cleared.
!
A minimum of one month's formal notice is mandatory for student withdrawal.

General Discipline Rules

1
Maintain discipline and respect towards teachers, staff, and fellow students at all times.
2
Bullying, ragging, or any form of harassment is strictly prohibited.
3
School property must be treated with care. Damage will be charged to the student.
4
Students must not leave the school premises during school hours without written permission.
5
Eating is only permitted during the designated lunch/snack break.
Empyrean International School
Dress Code

Regular Uniform (Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday)

ForUniform
GirlsBlue Skirt, Blue Leggy, Sky Blue Shirt with thin lining, Black & White Ribbon
BoysBlue Pants, Sky Blue Shirt with thin lining
Common – FootwearBlack & White Shoes, Blue & White Socks
Common – TieRed Line Tie
Winter WearBlue Koti and Navy Blue Sweater / Blazer

Special Uniform (Wednesday and Saturday)

ItemDescription
AttireRed T-shirt and Blue Lower
FootwearWhite Shoes and White Socks

Grooming & Uniform Rules

1
Complete prescribed uniform must be worn every day. No partial uniform permitted.
2
All clothing must be clean, neatly ironed, and properly labelled with student's name and class.
3
Hair must be neatly combed. Girls with long hair must plait or tie it neatly.
4
No jewellery of any kind is permitted. The school is not responsible for loss of jewellery or valuables.
5
No make-up or nail polish is permitted.
6
Students not in proper uniform may be sent home to change.
Empyrean International School
Attendance Policy

Minimum Attendance Requirement

As per MP Board norms, a student must maintain a minimum of 75% attendance to be eligible to appear in examinations.

Absence Procedure

1
Parents must call the school or inform in writing on the first day of absence.
2
A written leave application signed by parent/guardian must be submitted when the student returns.
3
A medical certificate is required for illness-related absence of more than 2 consecutive days.
4
Leave for personal/family reasons must be applied for in advance in the student diary.
5
Habitual late-coming will be treated as half-day absence and parents will be informed.
Empyrean International School
Mobile & Gadget Policy

Strict Prohibition

The possession or use of mobile phones or any electronic gadgets is STRICTLY PROHIBITED on school premises for all students (Nursery to Class 8).

1
If a mobile phone or electronic gadget is found, it will be confiscated immediately.
2
The device will be returned only to the parent/guardian after a formal meeting.
3
Second-time offenders may face suspension from school.
4
Earphones, smartwatches, gaming devices, and similar gadgets are also prohibited.
Empyrean International School
Parent Declaration

Declaration by the Parents / Guardian

I hereby declare that I have read and understood all the rules and information of the school as mentioned above, and I undertake to follow them strictly.

I strictly undertake NOT to send my child to school with any kind of jewellery, excess money, or valuables. I acknowledge that the school will NOT be held responsible for the loss of any such items if they are sent against these rules.

I agree to abide by the academic, disciplinary, and financial policies of Empyrean International School and provide my consent for the generation of my ward's APAAR ID as per Government norms.
